+
 You may specify up to four@compile-time macro files+(or none at all)
 if you wish to make your own macro definitions available when
 compiling a ZIL\function+or\program#(options 4, 5).

+Macro files must be sequential data sets or PDS members of
 interpretive LISP source code.

 Macro definitions may be accessed under the interpreter by loading them
 via the ZIL (LOAD) function.  You can include this in your INIT file,
 or you can put your macro definitions into your INIT file directly.
